        <name xml:lang="en">clay</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. This value represents the amount of various types of clay used for the production of 1 kg of clay roof tile, according to measurements and the information provided by the owner of the factory. The types of clay used are "tierra cera", "tierra negra", "tierra roja" and "tierra amarilla". "Tierra roja" is also known as "sandy".</comment>
