        <name xml:lang="en">Particulate Matter, &gt; 2.5 um and &lt; 10um</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated value. Multiplying the kg of fuel (wood) per kg of clay tile by the emission factor of the pollutant (kg/kg). Based on literature calculations and information provided by the owners of the factories. Particulate matter emission is produced from combustion of wood during the firing process. PM10 emission is produced from combustion of wood during the firing process. Particulate matter is &lt; 10 um. Reference: Jaya Sucozhañay, J. L., &amp; Gomezcoello Vásquez, J. L. (2012). Análisis comparativo de la contaminación atmosférica producida por la combustión en ladrilleras artesanales utilizando tres tipos de combustibles (Bachelor's thesis).</comment>
